  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Freezing of Gait relief</measure>
    <time_frame>At time of intervention (seconds)</time_frame>
    <description>We hypothesise that the intervention should provide Instantaneous relief from freezing and only be required during freezing. The intervention will be applied at each freezing event. There may be a training effect that could last for a unknown period, based on other stimulus type published by other groups this can be up to 1 month.</description>
